wdi2-SL.EMP.TOTL.SP.ZS.def: Employment to population ratio is the proportion of a country's population that is employed. Employment is defined as persons of working age who, during a short reference period, were engaged in any activity to produce goods or provide services for pay or profit, whether at work during the reference period (i.e. who worked in a job for at least one hour) or not at work due to temporary absence from a job, or to working-time arrangements. Ages 15 and older are generally considered the working-age population.
wdi2-SL.EMP.TOTL.SP.ZS.name: Employment to population ratio, 15+
wdi2-SL.EMP.TOTL.SP.ZS.source: International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT database. Data retrieved on June 15, 2021.
